text: The Arabian Mau is a natural domestic cat breed originated from African wildcat. World Cat Federation (WCF) and Emirates Feline Federation (EFF) have cat breed standards of Arabian Mau. == Appearance == The head is an elongated oval from top to bottom. The nose is slightly curved. The eyes are oval, large, and slanted. The eye color varies, and they usually have green eyes. The ears are large and tilted forward. == References == Category:Arabian Peninsula Category:Cat breeds Category:Natural cat breeds
